Hi Sam,
Excited to share the live platform with you: https://sow.qandu.me (using my own APIs and domain for now until you test it and approve).
ðŸš€ The Complete Journey - Discovery to Delivery:
1. Create Client Workspace
Each new client gets their own workspace. Behind the scenes, this automatically creates an isolated AI environment where all client-specific conversations and documents are storedâ€”keeping everything organized and context-aware.
2. Generate Statement of Work
Click "Create SOW" and chat with the AI. Describe your project scope, target audience, deliverablesâ€”anything relevant. The AI understands your business context and generates a fully-formatted SOW with:
Professional sections (Overview, Deliverables, Outcomes, Timeline)
Interactive pricing table with drag-to-reorder roles
Auto-calculated GST and totals
Editable rich-text content
3. Inline AI Editor - Two Powerful Ways to Work:
a) Highlight & Transform âœ¨
Select any text in the editor, and you get instant AI actions:
Improve Writing - Enhance clarity and flow
Fix Grammar - Correct errors automatically
Make Shorter/Longer - Adjust length precisely
Change Tone - Switch between professional/casual
Bulletize - Convert to bullet points
Summarize - Create concise summary
Add Examples - Include relevant examples
Rewrite - Fresh take on the content
The AI only modifies your selected text, leaving everything else untouched. Perfect for quick edits without regenerating the entire document.
b) Slash Commands (/) âš¡
Type / anywhere in the editor to:
Insert AI-generated content from scratch
Continue writing from where you left off
Generate tables, sections, or specific content types
vs. GEN AI (Right Sidebar Chat):
GEN AI generates full documents from conversation, while the inline editor refines existing text. Use GEN for creating entire SOWs, use inline editor for polishing specific paragraphs.
4. Export & Share
Download PDF - Client-ready, beautifully formatted proposal
Share Portal Link - Interactive client portal (more below)
5. Client Portal (/portal/sow/[id])
Your client receives a professional, branded portal where they can:
View the complete SOW
See interactive pricing breakdown
Accept the proposal with one click
Ask questions via AI chat (trained on their specific SOW)
6. Dashboard Intelligence
Access the Master Dashboard for analyticsâ€”SOW metrics, client insights, and chat with AI about any workspace. It pulls context across all your clients to answer strategic questions like "Which clients need follow-up?" or "What's our total pipeline value?"
7. Gardner Studio (AI Specialists)
Since we've built this powerful editor and AI system, I created specialized AI agents designed for different tasks:
GEN - The Architect: Full SOW generation with strategic planning
Property Marketing Pro: Real estate/property marketing campaigns
Ad Copy Machine: Facebook/Google ad copy optimized for CTR
CRM Communication Specialist: Email sequences, nurture campaigns
Case Study Crafter: Client success stories and testimonials
Landing Page Persuader: High-converting landing page copy
SEO Content Strategist: Blog posts, pillar content, keyword research
Proposal & Audit Specialist: Audits, RFP responses, strategy docs
Each one has specialized knowledge and generates content tailored to that specific need.
8. Admin Panel ðŸ”§
Access the admin dashboard at https://sow.qandu.me/admin where you can:
Manage Services: Edit your service catalog, pricing, and categories
Configure AI Models: Choose which AI models power the inline editor (60+ models available including free options like Gemini 2.0 Flash)
Customize Quick Actions: Add/edit/remove the inline editor shortcuts to match your workflow
Control Everything: Full control over the AI behavior, prompts, and system settings
ðŸ’¡ Side Note - SmartQuote Integration Opportunity
If everything looks solid and you'd like to take this even further, I've analyzed integrating SmartQuote (the project George mentioned).
SmartQuote is an AI-assisted quoting tool that:
Suggests tasks/services based on similar past jobs (using AI similarity matching)
Shows historical time/cost data (min/avg/max from completed projects)
Calculates margins in real-time as you adjust hours/rates
Exports directly to WorkflowMax or converts to SOW
The good news: The platform is already ~70% ready for this. We have the pricing calculator, service catalog database, AI engine, and client portal infrastructure. It would add an intelligent "Quote Builder" that learns from your past projects and helps you price new ones faster and more accuratelyâ€”reducing quote-to-close time significantly.
